article.headline: Valparaiso 68, Centenary 50
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. (AP) -- Samuel Haanpaa scored 20 points on 6-of-12 shooting to lead Valparaiso to a 68-50 victory over Centenary on Saturday. Haanpaa shot 5-of-8 from 3-point range and grabbed four rebounds. Urule Igbavboa had 15 points and seven rebounds and Shawn Huff added 11 points for the Crusaders (12-11, 6-3 Mid-Continent Conference). Alexander Starr scored eight points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead the Gentlemen (7-17, 1-8) in their seventh straight loss. Tyrone Hamilton added eight points for Centenary but committed seven turnovers. The Gentlemen finished with 13 turnovers which the Crusaders turned into 17 points. Centenary was held to 15-of-55 (27 percent) shooting from the floor and was outrebounded 42-33.
